race.comment: TAKA SPEED (6) resumes and kicking off over 1500m won't bother with three jumpouts under the saddle. He missed a whisker at Cranbourne over 1400m at his only fresh outing and was spelled off a 2L defeat in a 64 in town as a $2.8F. Needs a good ride from the awkward gate, but he rates strongly and has scope for more improvement. NORWOODS (3) races forward and deserved his win here this grade/distance. Carries 2kg more, but is still on an upward trajectory and should be right in it. MYSTIC VAMP (12) was narrowly beaten in the same contest, positioned on speed. Strips fitter again, and the 2kg claimer will use the inside barrier. Has to be considered. LIM'S SMYTHE (2) disappointed as a $3F at Pakenham after surprising there at big odds prior. Has been kept up to the mark with a jumpout, and Nolen stays aboard. May show more today.
